            <title>[HBASE-1312] ZooKeeper: Master&apos;s ephemeral node went away while it was still up and functioning normally</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1312</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Does the master watch its own znode? Right around the time of regionserver problems described in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1311&quot; title=&quot;ZooKeeperWrapper: Failed to set watcher on ZNode /hbase/master&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-1311&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-1311&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, clients could no longer find the master, but according to its log it was up and functionling normally. I think the master and regionserver sessions expired at the same time, as they were started within seconds of each other.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
